<table id="featured" class="mainpagebox">
<tbody><tr>
<th>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Featured_article">Featured article</span></h2>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td style="position:relative">
<div style="padding:3px 8px 2px">
<div style="margin-bottom:1.66em"><div class="mainpage-image-wrapper" style="float:left;clear:left;background:#fff;--darkbg:#222;border:1px solid #3B587E;margin:0 0.7em 0.2em 0">
<a href="/File:MSM-NAboxart.png" class="image"><img alt="The front North American cover for Mario Sports Mix" src="https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/c/c2/MSM-NAboxart.png/100px-MSM-NAboxart.png" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="100" height="141" srcset="https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/c/c2/MSM-NAboxart.png/150px-MSM-NAboxart.png 1.5x, https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/c/c2/MSM-NAboxart.png/200px-MSM-NAboxart.png 2x" data-file-width="1000" data-file-height="1410" /></a></div>
<i><b><a href="/Mario_Sports_Mix" title="Mario Sports Mix">Mario Sports Mix</a></b></i> is a <i><a href="/Super_Mario_(franchise)" title="Super Mario (franchise)">Super Mario</a></i> <a href="/Genre#Sports" title="Genre">sports</a> game for the <a href="/Wii" title="Wii">Wii</a> and an indirect follow-up to the basketball game <i><a href="/Mario_Hoops_3-on-3" title="Mario Hoops 3-on-3">Mario Hoops 3-on-3</a></i>. The main difference from before is that <a href="/Mario" title="Mario">Mario</a> and other player characters can not only compete in basketball, but also three other sports: hockey, dodgeball, and volleyball. The <i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Final_Fantasy" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Final Fantasy">Final Fantasy</a></i> characters from <i>Mario Hoops 3-on-3</i> also return, and <a href="/Slime_(Dragon_Quest)" title="Slime (Dragon Quest)">Slime</a>, a <i><a href="https://dragon-quest.org/wiki/Dragon_Quest_(series)" class="extiw" title="dragonquest:Dragon Quest (series)">Dragon Quest</a></i> mascot, was added as one of the player characters. This game was developed by <a href="/Square_Enix" title="Square Enix">Square Enix</a>, who also developed <i>Mario Hoops 3-on-3</i>.</div>
<div class="noprint" style="float:right;position:absolute;right:0;bottom:0;padding:0 17px 2px 0"><b><a href="/MarioWiki:Featured_articles" title="MarioWiki:Featured articles">More featured articles...</a></b></div>
</div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
