<th>
<h2><span id="Mario_&amp;_Nintendo_news"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Mario_.26_Nintendo_news">Mario &amp; Nintendo news</span></h2>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>
<div style="padding:0 8px 1px 0;margin-top:-1px">
<div><div class="mainpage-image-wrapper" style="float:right;clear:right;background:#fff;--darkbg:#222;border:1px solid #3B587E;margin:0 0 0.2em 0.7em">
<a href="/File:Play_Nintendo_MKT_Mobile_Game_Release_Date_banner.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Banner from a Mario Kart Tour release announcement" src="https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/e/e8/Play_Nintendo_MKT_Mobile_Game_Release_Date_banner.jpg/150px-Play_Nintendo_MKT_Mobile_Game_Release_Date_banner.jpg" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="150" height="52" srcset="https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/e/e8/Play_Nintendo_MKT_Mobile_Game_Release_Date_banner.jpg/225px-Play_Nintendo_MKT_Mobile_Game_Release_Date_banner.jpg 1.5x, https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/e/e8/Play_Nintendo_MKT_Mobile_Game_Release_Date_banner.jpg/300px-Play_Nintendo_MKT_Mobile_Game_Release_Date_banner.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1200" data-file-height="412" /></a></div>
<ul><li>On July 8, 2026, the end of service for <i><b><a href="/Mario_Kart_Tour" title="Mario Kart Tour">Mario Kart Tour</a></b> (pictured)</i> was announced for September 30, 2026.</li>
<li><i><b><a href="/Wario_Land:_Super_Mario_Land_3" title="Wario Land: Super Mario Land 3">Wario Land: Super Mario Land 3</a></b></i> and <i><b><a href="/Dr._Mario_%26_Puzzle_League" title="Dr. Mario &amp; Puzzle League">Dr. Mario &amp; Puzzle League</a></b></i> were released on <a href="/Game_Boy_-_Nintendo_Classics" title="Game Boy - Nintendo Classics">Game Boy - Nintendo Classics</a> and <a href="/Game_Boy_Advance_-_Nintendo_Classics" title="Game Boy Advance - Nintendo Classics">Game Boy Advance - Nintendo Classics</a> respectively on July 7, 2026.</li>
<li><a href="/Mario_Kart_World_(Nintendo_Music)" title="Mario Kart World (Nintendo Music)">16 music tracks</a> from  <i><b><a href="/Mario_Kart_World" title="Mario Kart World">Mario Kart World</a></b></i> that arrange music from <i><a href="/Super_Mario_World" title="Super Mario World">Super Mario World</a></i>, <i><a href="/Super_Mario_Land" title="Super Mario Land">Super Mario Land</a></i>, <i><a href="/Super_Mario_Land_2_-_6_Golden_Coins" title="Super Mario Land 2 - 6 Golden Coins">Super Mario Land 2 - 6 Golden Coins</a></i>, and <i>Wario Land: Super Mario Land 3</i> were made available on the <a href="/Nintendo_Music" title="Nintendo Music">Nintendo Music</a> app on July 6, 2026.</li>
<li>Ver. 1.7.0 of <i><b>Mario Kart World</b></i> was released on June 30, 2026, which adds the <a href="/Drill_Rally" title="Drill Rally">Drill</a> and <a href="/Boomerang_Rally_(Mario_Kart_World)" title="Boomerang Rally (Mario Kart World)">Boomerang Rally</a> to <a href="/Mario_Kart_World#Knockout_Tour" title="Mario Kart World">Knockout Tour</a>, <a href="/List_of_stickers_in_Mario_Kart_World#List_of_stickers" title="List of stickers in Mario Kart World">stickers</a> to <a href="/Photo_Mode" title="Photo Mode">Photo Mode</a>, and support for the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thai_language" class="extiw" title="wikipedia:Thai language">Thai language</a>.</li></ul></div>
</div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<table id="dyk" class="mainpagebox">
<tbody><tr>
<th>
<h2><span id="Did_you_know?"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Did_you_know.3F">Did you know?</span></h2>
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>
<div style="padding:0 8px 1px 0;margin-top:-2px">
<div><div class="mainpage-image-wrapper" style="float:right;clear:right;background:#fff;--darkbg:#222;border:1px solid #3B587E;margin:0 0 0.2em 0.7em">
<a href="/File:Fds_famicomgolfuscourse_jp.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Golf: US Course" src="https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/2/2e/Fds_famicomgolfuscourse_jp.jpg/100px-Fds_famicomgolfuscourse_jp.jpg" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="100" height="117" srcset="https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/2/2e/Fds_famicomgolfuscourse_jp.jpg/150px-Fds_famicomgolfuscourse_jp.jpg 1.5x, https://mario.wiki.gallery/images/thumb/2/2e/Fds_famicomgolfuscourse_jp.jpg/200px-Fds_famicomgolfuscourse_jp.jpg 2x" data-file-width="565" data-file-height="661" /></a></div>
<ul><li><i><b><a href="/Golf:_US_Course" title="Golf: US Course">Golf: US Course</a></b></i> <i>(pictured)</i> is the first game in the <i><a href="/Super_Mario_(franchise)" title="Super Mario (franchise)">Super Mario</a></i> franchise to support more than two players.</li>
<li>The <b><a href="/Mario_Quiz_Cards" title="Mario Quiz Cards">Mario Quiz Cards</a></b> feature an illustration of a character from the <i>Super Mario</i> franchise with a speech bubble that asks a multiple-choice question that covers a wide variety of topics.</li>
<li>In the <a href="/Mario%27s_Time_Machine_(PC)" title="Mario&#39;s Time Machine (PC)">PC</a> and <a href="/Mario%27s_Time_Machine_(Super_Nintendo_Entertainment_System)" title="Mario&#39;s Time Machine (Super Nintendo Entertainment System)">SNES releases of <i>Mario's Time Machine</i></a>, <a href="/Bowser" title="Bowser">Bowser</a> steals the <b><a href="/Declaration_of_Independence" title="Declaration of Independence">Declaration of Independence</a></b> before it can be signed. <a href="/Mario" title="Mario">Mario</a> retrieves it from <a href="/Bowser%27s_Museum" title="Bowser&#39;s Museum">Bowser's Museum</a> and travels back to <a href="/Philadelphia" title="Philadelphia">Philadelphia</a> to return it.</li>
<li>At the end of every <a href="/Level" title="Level">level</a> in <i><a href="/Super_Mario_Bros." title="Super Mario Bros.">Super Mario Bros.</a></i> except <a href="/Castle" title="Castle">castle</a> levels, <b><a href="/Fireworks" title="Fireworks">fireworks</a></b> go off when <a href="/Mario" title="Mario">Mario</a> or <a href="/Luigi" title="Luigi">Luigi</a> enters the <a href="/Fortress" title="Fortress">fortress</a> if the last number in the timer when hitting the <a href="/Goal_Pole" title="Goal Pole">flagpole</a> is either a 1, a 3, or a 6; the number of fireworks is equal to the last digit of the timer.</li></ul></div>
</div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
